                  <h3 class="content-text">AI & ML:</h3>
                  <ul style="list-style: none;">
                     <li>
                        <a href="https://github.com/t6nand/source-separation">Source separation using Deep Learning.</a> 
                        <ul style="padding-left: 20px">
                           <li>This project presents an implementation and evaluation of an end-to-end system based on deep learning for speech enhancement based audio source separation. 
                              Speech Enhancement is achieved by predicting and applying a ratio mask to a time-frequency representation of the noisy audio signal and through a subsequent reconstruction of the estimated clean speech signal.
                              The project compared different implementations of supervised deep learning systems that can learn to enhance speech from background noise in monaural (single microphone) recordings.
                           </li>
                        </ul>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <a href="https://github.com/t6nand/mltasks/blob/master/task1.ipynb">CIFAR-10 Dataset Image classification based on CNN</a>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <a href="https://github.com/t6nand/mltasks/blob/master/task2.ipynb">MCMC Sampling for a very large data constellation.</a>
                        <ul style="padding-left: 20px">
                           <li>
                              The Markov Chain Monte Carlo sampling is a very efficient method to sample the data from a large contellation size. In this mini project, a MIMO transceiver with N t = N r = 2 and N t = N r = 8 and 16-QAM was considered.
                              Note that for example if a higher dimensional QAM constellation is considered, calculating the log-likelihood values becomes infeasible. 
                              For example, for 64-QAM and Nt = 8 antennas we have Nt = 64^8 = 2^48 ≈ 10^14. An approach to circumvent this complexity was demonstrated by using MCMC sampling.
                              
                           </li>
                        </ul>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <a href="https://github.com/t6nand/mltasks/blob/master/task3.ipynb">Unsupervised Learning based blind parameter estimation of a receiver in communication system.</a>
                        <ul style="padding-left: 20px"> 
                           <li>
                              Used K-Means algorithm to first find out the constellation of the communication system. Post, using the K-Means results, initialised the expectation maximization (EM) algorithm to determine the unknown
                              model parameters and the distribution of the constellation symbols.
                           </li>
                        </ul>
                     </li>
